In the directory /tmp/sv-b1c01b79830c4728a5ca0d59b64ef134/before, fix 4 LRO files that use `ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>()` which triggers IL2026/IL3050 AOT warnings.

The 4 files are:
1. ManagementGroup/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ManagementGroupsArmOperation.cs
2. ManagementGroup/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ManagementGroupsArmOperationOfT.cs
3. Resources/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ResourcesArmOperation.cs
4. Resources/Generated/LongRunningOperation/ResourcesArmOperationOfT.cs

In each file, line 61 has:
```csharp
var lroDetails = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default).ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>();
return lroDetails["id"];
```

Replace with an AOT-safe approach using JsonDocument:
```csharp
var lroData = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default);
using var lroDocument = JsonDocument.Parse(lroData);
return lroDocument.RootElement.GetProperty("id").GetString();
```

Make sure `using System.Text.Json;` is present in each file. Add it if needed.

Also, the variable `lroDetails` was only used to get `["id"]`, so the replacement removes that variable entirely and replaces the `return lroDetails["id"]` on the next line.

Actually, looking more carefully - the full pattern in the method is:
```csharp
private string GetOperationId(RehydrationToken? rehydrationToken)
{
    if (rehydrationToken is null)
    {
        return null;
    }
    var lroDetails = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default).ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>();
    return lroDetails["id"];
}
```

Replace the two lines (lroDetails assignment and return) with:
```csharp
    var lroData = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default);
    using var lroDocument = JsonDocument.Parse(lroData);
    return lroDocument.RootElement.GetProperty("id").GetString();
```

Do this for all 4 files.

